<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05017e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05017e">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05017e"> 17(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> King of Nations</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In the next chapter we find Lot living in Sodom, and getting into trouble there. Amraphel king of Shinar, Arioch king of Ellassar, Chedorlaomer king of Elam, and Tidal <mark>&ldquo;king of nations,&rdquo;</mark> made war with Bera king of Sodom, Birsha king of Gomorrah, Shinab king of Admah, Shemeber king of Zeboiim, and the &ldquo;king of Bela which is Zoar.&rdquo; <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="BROM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BROM"><cite title="source">Bible Romances</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1922) [Lot&apos;s Wife] 85</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
